<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Fleet xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
  <Name>Verdant Wing</Name>
  <Version>3</Version>
  <TotalPoints>3000</TotalPoints>
  <FactionKey>KUIPER/kuiper</FactionKey>
  <Description>Difficulty: &lt;color=red&gt;HARD&lt;/color&gt;

Verdant Wing "Dark Forest" is a long range indirect/direct missile strike wing. 'An Uncomfortable Truth' and 'A Convenient Lie' are two MkII Cadonia class missile frigates, able to be used as a pair or operate independently. Loaded in their tubes are an array of missiles:
The SDM-227 Gale ACM. A general purpose anti craft missile, capable of shooting down most fighters or bombers in a single good hit.
A single SGM-H-35 Squall ACM. A heavy anti-craft weapon, capable of wiping out an entire flight of craft in ideal situations, but requires manual targeting.
The SGM-H-302 Peck ASM. Intended to act as a one shot, one kill, weapon against corvette and frigate equivalents, while retaining some effectiveness into medium weight targets. 
The SGM-265 Roadkill ASM. Intended to act as a long range direct weapon against corvette and frigate equivalents in salvo sizes of 6, while retaining some effectiveness into medium weight targets. 
Next, the SGM-H-320 Talon - A, SGM-H-320 Talon - B, and SGM-H-320 Talon - C. This Trio of missiles are intended to be fired as a group and produce devastating effects on lighter targets, such as the 'Marauder' lineship. They are also cruise capable, allowing them to strike targets out of line of sight of the Cadonias, even without a track. 
Of particular note are the SGM-H-316 Rending Claw - A, SGM-H-316 Rending Claw - B, and SGM-H-316 Rending Claw - C. This Trio of missiles are intended to be fired as a group and produce devastating effects on heavy cruisers or battleships. They are also cruise capable through use of Target Reference Points (TRPs) allowing them to strike targets out of line of sight of the Cadonias as long as a ship is providing a track. 
Included with the Cadonias are a pair of spotter/jammer Kyves. Both able to provide good fire solutions for the missiles of the Cadonias as well as supporting them through electronic warfare. Verdant wing has the potential to reap a grim toll against the enemy's heavy assets.
  </Description>
  <SortOverrideOrder>7</SortOverrideOrder>
  <ModDependencies>
    <unsignedLong>3649434947</unsignedLong>
  </ModDependencies>
